track_notes: Ramsey Peak is a long hike from the Ramsey Vista Campground, with more than 12 miles round trip, 4,600 feet of gross elevation gain during the round trip, and maximum slope of 24%. The summit is reached via a combination of trails and bushwhacking to the summit.
track_title: Ramsey Peak via Ramsey Vista Campground

track_notes: This is a tough hike with 20.2 miles total distance and quite a lot of elevation gain (and loss) that leaves your legs sore.  If you had enough time and energy, this route goes right past the summit of W7A/CO-001, Carr Peak and you could add it as well.
